1147
01:36:58,062 --> 01:37:00,485
Let me tell you somethin',
sweetheart.

1148
01:37:02,734 --> 01:37:04,953
You're very good at your job.

1149
01:37:17,165 --> 01:37:20,044
You mean I was workin'
for a guy from the mailroom?

1150
01:37:20,126 --> 01:37:23,300
- You're not an executive?
- He's too good to be an executive.

1151
01:37:24,422 --> 01:37:26,390
- Disappointed?
- Yes!

1152
01:37:26,466 --> 01:37:29,015
I was having fun on this job.

1153
01:37:29,093 --> 01:37:33,189
You had all this energy,
and all these crazy ideas.

1154
01:37:33,264 --> 01:37:35,358
And you kept takin'
your pants off.

1155
01:37:35,433 --> 01:37:37,731
I don't want you to go.

1156
01:37:38,936 --> 01:37:40,563
Here.

1157
01:37:40,938 --> 01:37:43,236
Just a little somethin'
to remember me by.

1158
01:37:44,025 --> 01:37:47,279
- Thank you.
- Brantley, why you lookin' so sad?

1159
01:37:47,945 --> 01:37:50,698
I don't know. I just thought
it'd work out better, you know?

1160
01:37:50,823 --> 01:37:52,450
The job or the girl?

1161
01:37:53,576 --> 01:37:56,500
The job. To hell with the girl.

1162
01:37:57,121 --> 01:38:00,091
Yeah.
You sound real convincing.

1163
01:38:00,958 --> 01:38:03,256
Well, look at it this way, pal.

1164
01:38:04,379 --> 01:38:08,134
For a few weeks, you sat up here in
the lofty atmosphere of the big cheeses.

1165
01:38:08,257 --> 01:38:12,057
You had a nice view of Manhattan
and a clean lunchroom to eat in.

1166
01:38:12,136 --> 01:38:15,936
Hell, you did more in two months
than most people do in a lifetime.

1167
01:38:16,933 --> 01:38:18,935
Yeah, I'm gonna miss it.

1168
01:38:19,977 --> 01:38:22,480
The job or the girl?

1169
01:38:30,655 --> 01:38:33,659
- Goin' back to Kansas?
- No, I'm not goin' back to Kansas.

1170
01:38:33,741 --> 01:38:35,459
I came to New York to succeed.

1171
01:38:35,576 --> 01:38:37,624
I hear there's an opening
in the mailroom.

1172
01:38:37,703 --> 01:38:40,627
You should talk.
You're just as unemployed as I am.

1173
01:38:40,706 --> 01:38:42,708
Not for long.
I have contacts all over town.

1174
01:38:42,792 --> 01:38:45,919
- There's always another Prescott around.
- Low blow, Foster. Dirty pool.

1175
01:38:45,920 --> 01:38:48,240
- I call 'em like I see 'em.
- Yeah, you're perfect, right?

1176
01:38:48,339 --> 01:38:51,020
- I never slept with the boss.
- No, you slept with the boss's wife.

1177
01:38:51,092 --> 01:38:52,469
She seduced me.

1178
01:38:52,593 --> 01:38:54,436
He seduced me.
What's the difference?

1179
01:38:54,512 --> 01:38:56,765
I couldn't help it.
You went willingly.

1180
01:38:56,848 --> 01:38:59,727
- I see. You were tied up in chains.
- I'll tell you what the difference is.

1181
01:38:59,809 --> 01:39:02,107
- I thought you were a nice guy.
- Lam a nice guy!

1182
01:39:02,186 --> 01:39:03,603
You're a rat!

1183
01:39:03,604 --> 01:39:05,481
You lied to me, deceived me,
then acted as judge and jury...

1184
01:39:05,565 --> 01:39:07,238
in a situation
you knew nothing about.

1185
01:39:07,316 --> 01:39:10,661
- I know you were spying on me.
- I wasn't spying on you!

1186
01:39:10,736 --> 01:39:14,206
- And I won't be spying on you any more!
- No, you won't, 'cause if I see you...

1187
01:39:22,832 --> 01:39:25,130
Sorry. This car is full.

1188
01:39:30,256 --> 01:39:32,850
- We could never pull that off.
- How do you know?

1189
01:39:32,925 --> 01:39:35,644
I'm a kid from the mailroom
who moved into a top executive position.

1190
01:39:35,761 --> 01:39:37,559
Are you gonna tell me
I can't pull it off?

1191
01:39:37,638 --> 01:39:39,231
But you didn't.

1192
01:39:39,724 --> 01:39:43,228
I almost did.
We could pull this off.

1193
01:39:45,563 --> 01:39:48,817
- I'm gonna need your help, both of you.
- Ls it somethin' I could get fired for?

1194
01:39:48,900 --> 01:39:51,109
- Absolutely.
- I like it.

1195
01:39:51,110 --> 01:39:53,954
<i>Jean,</i> see if you can find
Harley McMasters' phone number.

1196
01:39:54,071 --> 01:39:56,574
And get some food up here.
Chinese sound good to you?

1197
01:39:57,825 --> 01:40:01,580
Mr Davenport, we realize you'll want
to move some of your own people...

1198
01:40:01,662 --> 01:40:05,417
into the medium control
positions here at Pemrose.

1199
01:40:07,835 --> 01:40:09,132
Naturally.

1200
01:40:10,087 --> 01:40:14,012
What we're concerned about, frankly,
is the upper management positions.

1201
01:40:16,719 --> 01:40:20,144
- Most of'em will have to go.
- Oh, no.

1202
01:40:22,225 --> 01:40:23,772
I see.

1203
01:40:25,853 --> 01:40:28,231
But a handful of'em...

1204
01:40:29,732 --> 01:40:31,655
who have been so helpful...

1205
01:40:33,736 --> 01:40:35,955
like yourselves, of course...

1206
01:40:36,781 --> 01:40:38,829
will be stayin'
as long <i>as</i> you like.

1207
01:40:40,451 --> 01:40:42,419
Well, then I see nothing
to stand in the way...

1208
01:40:42,495 --> 01:40:45,044
of the immediate merger
of our two companies.

1209
01:40:45,122 --> 01:40:48,171
Is this the place? It is!
Hey, good. Sorry we're late.

1210
01:40:48,251 --> 01:40:52,176
- Get them out of here.
- I'm sorry. This is a private meeting.

1211
01:40:52,255 --> 01:40:55,805
- I have to ask you to leave.
- Hold these, will you? Thanks a lot.

1212
01:40:58,553 --> 01:41:01,352
- Call building security.
- Howard, relax. Listen.

1213
01:41:01,430 --> 01:41:03,524
On behalf of the personnel
in the mailroom...

1214
01:41:03,599 --> 01:41:06,773
the girls in the secretarial pool,
the female executives here at Pemrose...

1215
01:41:06,852 --> 01:41:08,932
we wanted to give our blessing
to this little merger.

1216
01:41:08,938 --> 01:41:12,784
- Who in hell are these people?
- Ls that Don? Donny!

1217
01:41:12,858 --> 01:41:16,863
How ya doin'? You mind if I stand up?
I think better when I'm movin' around.

1218
01:41:16,946 --> 01:41:18,744
Gotta tell you, Don...

1219
01:41:18,823 --> 01:41:20,825
at first, the idea of this merger
made me as nervous...

1220
01:41:20,908 --> 01:41:23,832
as a long-tailed cat
in a room full of rocking chairs.

1221
01:41:23,911 --> 01:41:26,209
But then I realized
I was wrong.

1222
01:41:26,330 --> 01:41:29,675
The combination of our products
and your distribution capabilities...

1223
01:41:29,750 --> 01:41:32,879
could vault Pemrose
right to the top of the market.

1224
01:41:33,879 --> 01:41:36,007
So glad you approve...

1225
01:41:36,424 --> 01:41:38,017
whoever you are.

1226
01:41:38,092 --> 01:41:40,595
Now if you get the hell out of here,
we'll finish the job.

1227
01:41:41,095 --> 01:41:42,972
I can't do that for you, Don.

1228
01:41:43,848 --> 01:41:46,067
See, the problem here
is management.

1229
01:41:47,059 --> 01:41:49,403
Things were bad enough
when Howard was running the company.

1230
01:41:49,404 --> 01:41:53,696
- Now we got you to deal with too.
- Get them out of here, now.

1231
01:41:53,774 --> 01:41:57,028
He can't, Don. You see,
Brantley made arrangements...

1232
01:41:57,111 --> 01:41:59,113
to buy five percent
of the stock...

1233
01:41:59,196 --> 01:42:02,075
in your company,
Davenport Enterprises, this morning.

1234
01:42:03,200 --> 01:42:05,623
- We're buying you out.
- What?

1235
01:42:05,703 --> 01:42:07,501
Get in there!

1236
01:42:08,456 --> 01:42:10,208
That's right!

1237
01:42:10,875 --> 01:42:13,674
We've initiated a takeover
of Davenport Enterprises...

1238
01:42:13,753 --> 01:42:16,552
in a proxy fight
for the Pemrose Corporation.

1239
01:42:16,672 --> 01:42:20,427
- This <i>way,</i> Mr McMasters.
- Gentlemen, good afternoon.

1240
01:42:20,509 --> 01:42:22,927
These are
my financial advisers.

1241
01:42:22,928 --> 01:42:25,977
They agreed to lend me the money
to finance this takeover.

1242
01:42:26,057 --> 01:42:28,731
Surely you're not going to invest
in some crackpot scheme...

1243
01:42:28,851 --> 01:42:32,192
cooked up by a kid
who used to work in our mailroom.

1244
01:42:32,193 --> 01:42:35,533
Not at first, <i>Howie,</i>
but I had an ace in the hole:

1245
01:42:35,650 --> 01:42:38,824
A major stockholder in the company
with the clout and support I needed.

1246
01:42:38,903 --> 01:42:40,997
Don, I want you to meet...

1247
01:42:41,072 --> 01:42:44,121
the new chairperson
of the Pemrose Corporation...

1248
01:42:44,200 --> 01:42:46,453
and the daughter of the founder...

1249
01:42:46,454 --> 01:42:48,295
Vera Prescott.

1250
01:42:50,790 --> 01:42:53,634
Afternoon,
ladies and gentlemen.

1251
01:42:53,709 --> 01:42:55,677
Brantley and I
are very old friends...

1252
01:42:55,753 --> 01:42:58,882
and when he told me his wonderful
ideas for running the company...

1253
01:42:58,964 --> 01:43:00,966
I knew he was
the man for the job.

1254
01:43:01,050 --> 01:43:05,647
I think we all understand
your real motivation here, Vera.

1255
01:43:07,640 --> 01:43:09,849
I admit I felt...

1256
01:43:09,850 --> 01:43:12,854
some attraction towards Brantley
at the beginning...

1257
01:43:12,937 --> 01:43:15,315
but <i>as</i> you've always
told me, Howard...

1258
01:43:15,398 --> 01:43:17,150
love is love...

1259
01:43:17,233 --> 01:43:19,452
but business is business.

1260
01:43:20,027 --> 01:43:22,780
You've run Daddy's company
into the ground, Howard...

1261
01:43:22,905 --> 01:43:26,205
and I believe these people here can
bring it back to where it belongs again.

1262
01:43:27,118 --> 01:43:30,122
Now, up, Howard,
out of that chair.

1263
01:43:30,871 --> 01:43:34,216
Don't be ridiculous.
I'm not about to resign my position.

1264
01:43:34,217 --> 01:43:38,088
You don't have to, Howard.
You're fired.

1265
01:43:38,170 --> 01:43:39,797
What?

1266
01:43:40,464 --> 01:43:42,842
- Vera, you can't!
- Yes, I can.

1267
01:43:43,008 --> 01:43:45,010
You see, Mr Davenport...

1268
01:43:45,094 --> 01:43:49,597
as of this afternoon,
I control 50.1 %% of the voting stock.

1269
01:43:49,598 --> 01:43:51,817
You, too, Art. You're history.

1270
01:43:55,479 --> 01:43:59,109
Brantley, Christy,
<i>Jean,</i> Melrose.

1271
01:44:08,242 --> 01:44:10,040
Gentlemen, just in time.

1272
01:44:10,119 --> 01:44:12,918
Mr Prescott and his aide have
disrupted a very important meeting.

1273
01:44:12,997 --> 01:44:15,091
Would you please escort them
out of the building?

1274
01:44:15,166 --> 01:44:18,045
Vera! Why this open hostility?

1275
01:44:18,127 --> 01:44:20,676
I don't understand.
How did you get so...

1276
01:44:20,796 --> 01:44:22,890
Would you take charge of
the meeting <i>now,</i> Brantley?

1277
01:44:22,965 --> 01:44:25,343
- What did I ever do to deserve this?
- Excuse me.

1278
01:44:35,936 --> 01:44:38,405
Feel free to do that
amongst yourselves if you want.

1279
01:44:42,359 --> 01:44:45,704
- So have you been to Kansas?
- No. What's in Kansas?

1280
01:44:45,821 --> 01:44:49,496
Well, I figured we'd take
the private Pemrose jet...

1281
01:44:49,575 --> 01:44:51,703
drop in on the folks.

1282
01:44:52,036 --> 01:44:54,038
They're gonna want to meet you.

1283
01:44:57,583 --> 01:44:59,881
Why haven't I met you before?

1284
01:44:59,960 --> 01:45:02,258
Baby, you ain't been hangin' out
in the mailroom.

1285
01:45:02,421 --> 01:45:05,174
The mailroom.
I like that sound.

1286
01:45:12,473 --> 01:45:15,773
Charlie, we got that same problem
with elevator three again.

1287
01:45:15,851 --> 01:45:18,024
I don't believe this.

1288
01:45:18,813 --> 01:45:20,565
This elevator's stuck again.

1289
01:46:24,044 --> 01:46:27,014
- Where to, sir?
- The opera, Rattigan.

1290
01:46:27,089 --> 01:46:29,592
Yes, sir.

